DovER CHARTERS 405

Mnyors and chamberlains of the said town for ever, the aforesaid plot of land with its appurtenances, into whomso- ever’s hands it may come.

In witness whereof as well the common scal as the scal of the aforoeaid Christopher Eliot are affixed to this indenture.

Given at Dover on the aforesaid day of the mouth of September in the third year of the reign of Lady Elizabeth‚ by the grace of God Queen of England, France‚ and Ireland, Defendet of the Faith. In the year 1561.
